    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.74"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection
                    78</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">74</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE ACADEMY OF AMERICAN POETS
                        <lb/>
                    890 PARK AVENUE
                        <lb/>
                    NEW YORK 21, N.Y.</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    
                    ∙THE ACADEMY OF AMERICAN POETS∙
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>A Winged Horse</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    25<hi rend="italics">th</hi> <hi rend="caps">YEAR</hi>
                    1934 ∙ 1959
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>March 20, 1959</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Professor John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim Farm, Route 6</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Professor Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Thank you so much for the good news that you <hi rend="underline">will</hi> edit poetry for Poetry Pilot.</p>
                
                <p>If it is convenient we would certainly like to schedule you for the May issue, which would mean having the poems by the middle of April. If you can not see your way to doing this, a month later would be all right too.</p>
                
                <p>May I remind you again that we would like six or eight poems of your selection, and if you do not have time to copy them for us, just give us the titles and authors, and if possible the books from which you have selected them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With much appreciation and best wishes, I am</salute>
                
                    <salute>Most sincerely yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Marie Bullock</signed>
                    <signed>Mrs. Hugh Bullock
                    President</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
